  "excerpt": "The UK average is 142 litres per person per day. Toilets account for 30%, showers and baths 25%, and washing machines 15%. A household audit uses appliance ratings and usage counts to build a use-by-activity breakdown and identify whether toilet, shower, or garden use is the dominant saving opportunity.",
